I disagree a bit there Epicure...<br>
<br>
<br>
A pickup raid isn't the same as a raid with a regular team.<br>
<br>
When your team has a bad day, you suck it up... you know tommorow your crew will have their @#%$ together.  You know your team well.... if someone is uncharacteristically being a flake, you know it's not the general rule for them.  Your team will be there to talk to as a group in game, on the boards ect after the fact to work out differences.   Now, on a pickup raid especially if you don't know the raiders well, it's much easier to get frustrated with mistakes, especially simple ones.  It's also more likely those mistakes are more the norm, if the raid crew is inexperienced.  You also simply don't have the connection/comraderie or loyalty to a bunch of guys trying to kill vox than you do your home team.<br>
<br>
As a leader of a guild/team raid, you know your crew and can assume and delegate things more.  You can't on a pickup.  You can't tell a pickup raid &quot;use standard wall positioning&quot;.  Or &quot;get yer buffs up as needed&quot;.   Pickup raids are hard.. even with the new chat system you need to micromanage a lot more.  On a pickup raid you also can't look at things in a long term effect.  A chanter you ask to come as the only chanter there is doing you a favor, usually.  Unless there is some personal history there from times past, that chanter is a key class that raid needs, and the Leader has to make sure the key classes are taken care of.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure I agree or disagree with what happened in this case.. I think the raid leader screwed up, and maybe the chanter left hasitly, but ... it was a pickup raid.  I don't know the individuals involved, and without knowing any history between them, I see no reason why the enchanter should feel obligated to stay and help if she was being ignored, intentionally or not.  It doesn't look like either side was out to screw the other, one side goofed and the other side was looking out for themselves first... both of which are part of the pickup raid game. <p>Gurunt Bangoo <Wraith>
